<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Using 'attribs' for the form blows the action key.  To get the form to generate properly, you have to move the action into the attribs array.</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$form = new Zend_Form(array(
    'action' =&gt; '/user/test',
    'method' =&gt; 'post',
    'elements' =&gt; array(
        'username' =&gt; 'text'
    )
));
</code></pre>

<p>Works. Form action is set in HTML.</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$form = new Zend_Form(array(
    'action' =&gt; '/user/test',
    'method' =&gt; 'post',
    'attribs' =&gt; array('id'=&gt;'testid', 'class'=&gt;'testclass'),
    'elements' =&gt; array(
        'username' =&gt; 'text'
    )
));
</code></pre>

<p>{color:red}<em>Doesn't Work. Form action is not set in HTML.</em>{color}</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$form = new Zend_Form(array(
    'method' =&gt; 'post',
    'attribs' =&gt; array('action'=&gt;'/user/test', 'id'=&gt;'testid', 'class'=&gt;
    'testclass'),
    'elements' =&gt; array(
        'username' =&gt; 'text'
    )
));
</code></pre>

<p>Works. Form action is set in HTML.</p>

